Distribution.
Corallium tricolor
is a rarely recorded species mainly distributed in the northeastern Atlantic Ocean. It has been reported from Morocco , the Canary Islands, the Cape Verde Islands, Madeira, and the Irving Seamount slope at 598–1090 m depth ( Johnson 1898 , 1899 ;
Grasshoff 1986
;
Brito & Ocaña 2004
;
Sampaio et al . 2009
).
